Review of: Private tour/ transfer from Hoi An/Da Nang to Golden Bridge
Written January 17, 2020
This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. Tripadvisor performs checks on reviews as part of our industry-leading trust & safety standards. Read our transparency report to learn more.
Odysseas R
Athens, Greece12 contributions
Tour to Hue, Hoi An, Golden Bridge (Da Nang)
We visited those 3 beautiful cities for our honeymoon and Vu was our guide. His knowledge is excellent, he is really friendly and made us feel welcome, like we had a friend traveling with us. His tours are excellent, straight to the point and he explained us a lot of things about the history of the cities, their traditions, their religion and the culture of Vietnam. He also guided us to the markets showing us the daily routine of the locals, which is very important in order to understand the Vietnamese culture (we are from Greece so their culture was totally unknown to us). We are very lucky that we had Vu as we believe that without him we would have missed the chance to have so many details about the buildings, the cities, the culture etc. His tips about restaurants and how to spend our free time were really valuable. If you ever visit those cities, we strongly recommend to contact him as he will add value to your trip
